---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Corgi Age Calculator — Dog to Human Years"
  description="Calculate your Corgi's age in human years with our highly accurate, breed-size based scientific formula. Fast, free, and no login required."
>
  <section class="container-custom py-10 sm:py-16 md:py-24 pb-20">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
      <p class="text-xs text-[var(--text-muted)] mb-2 sm:mb-4">
        <a href="/" class="text-[var(--text-faint)] hover:text-[var(--text-secondary)] transition-colors no-underline">Home</a>
        <span class="text-[var(--text-faint)] mx-1.5">›</span>
        <span class="text-[var(--text-secondary)]">Corgi Age Calculator</span>
      </p>
      <span class="inline-block text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-wider text-[var(--text-faint)] px-4 py-1.5 rounded-full border border-[var(--border-default)] mb-4 sm:mb-6">Breed Calculator</span>
      <h1 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4">Corgi Age Calculator — Dog to Human Years</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-[var(--text-secondary)] mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        Corgis (Pembroke Welsh Corgi and Cardigan Welsh Corgi) are medium-small herding breeds famous for their short legs and fox-like faces. Corgis are relatively long-lived for their size and beloved worldwide. Use our Corgi age calculator to find your dog's true human equivalent age.
      </p>

      <div class="card card-hover-lift p-4 sm:p-6 md:p-8 mb-8" id="breed-calc-root">
        <form id="breed-calc-form" class="space-y-6">
          <div>
            <label for="breed-name" class="block text-sm font-medium text-[var(--text-secondary)] mb-1">Your Dog's Name <span class="text-[var(--text-faint)]">(optional)</span></label>
            <input type="text" id="breed-name" class="input-base" placeholder="e.g. Nugget" maxlength="30" />
          </div>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            <div>
              <label for="breed-years" class="block text-sm font-medium text-[var(--text-secondary)] mb-1">Years</label>
              <input type="number" id="breed-years" class="input-base" placeholder="0" min="0" max="30" required />
            </div>
            <div>
              <label for="breed-months" class="block text-sm font-medium text-[var(--text-secondary)] mb-1">Months</label>
              <select id="breed-months" class="select-base">
                {Array.from({ length: 12 }, (_, i) => <option value={i}>{i === 0 ? '0 months' : i === 1 ? '1 month' : `${i} months`}</option>)}
              </select>
            </div>
          </div>
          <button type="submit" class="btn-primary w-full justify-center text-base py-4">🐾 Calculate Human Age</button>
        </form>

        <div id="breed-result" class="hidden mt-8 pt-8 border-t border-[var(--border-default)] text-center" aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true">
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] mb-1">Your Corgi is equivalent to</p>
          <p class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight text-[var(--text-primary)]" id="breed-human-age">—</p>
          <p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-[var(--text-secondary)] mt-2">human years old</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--text-secondary)] mt-4" id="breed-stage"></p>
          <p class="text-xs text-[var(--text-faint)] mt-2" id="breed-expectancy"></p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-block mt-6 text-sm text-[var(--color-link)] hover:underline">Try the full calculator with health timeline →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-center text-sm text-[var(--text-muted)] mb-12">
        <a href="/" class="text-[var(--color-link)] hover:underline">← Back to main Dog Age Calculator</a>
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-6 text-sm text-[var(--text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold tracking-tight text-[var(--text-primary)]">Corgi Age FAQ</h2>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-[var(--text-primary)] font-medium mb-1">How old is my Corgi in human years?</h3>
          <p>Enter your Corgi's age above. We use the DNA methylation formula (16 × ln(age) + 31) with a medium-breed multiplier, giving you a scientifically accurate human-equivalent age calibrated for the Corgi's unique size and aging profile.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-[var(--text-primary)] font-medium mb-1">What is the lifespan of a Corgi?</h3>
          <p>Pembroke and Cardigan Welsh Corgis typically live 12–15 years. They are considered relatively long-lived for medium-small dogs. Maintaining a healthy weight and protecting their spine are the two most important factors for longevity.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-[var(--text-primary)] font-medium mb-1">When is a Corgi considered a senior?</h3>
          <p>Corgis are generally considered seniors around age 10. At this point, bi-annual veterinary checkups are recommended, with particular focus on spinal health, joint function, weight, and any signs of degenerative myelopathy.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-[var(--text-primary)] font-medium mb-1">Do Corgis have back problems as they age?</h3>
          <p>Yes — Corgis are susceptible to Intervertebral Disc Disease (IVDD) due to their long bodies and short legs, the same vulnerability seen in Dachshunds. As Corgis age, disc degeneration can lead to pain or even paralysis. Keeping your Corgi lean, using ramps instead of stairs, and avoiding high-impact jumping are critical preventive measures.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-[var(--border-default)] space-y-4 text-sm text-[var(--text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold tracking-tight text-[var(--text-primary)]">Corgi Aging Guide</h2>
        <p>Corgis are medium-small herding breeds with a typical lifespan of 12–15 years. Originally bred to herd cattle in Wales, they are energetic, intelligent, and loyal dogs. Their distinctive body structure — long spine, short legs — is the defining factor in their age-related health risks.</p>
        <p>Their long back and short legs make Corgis susceptible to Intervertebral Disc Disease (IVDD), the same spinal vulnerability shared with Dachshunds. Weight management is critical — every extra pound places disproportionate stress on the spine. Use ramps or steps instead of having your Corgi jump on and off furniture or in and out of cars.</p>
        <p>Begin senior care from age 8–9 with bi-annual vet checkups that include a spinal assessment, joint evaluation, and bloodwork. Degenerative Myelopathy (DM) — a progressive spinal cord disease — is also more common in Corgis, particularly Pembrokes. Physical therapy and hydrotherapy can help manage mobility in aging Corgis. Keep them mentally stimulated and physically active at a safe, low-impact level throughout their senior years.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-[var(--border-default)]">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold tracking-tight text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-4 text-center">More Breed Calculators</h2>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-2">
          <a href="/labrador-age-calculator" class="tag-pill text-xs no-underline">Labrador</a>
          <a href="/golden-retriever-age-calculator" class="tag-pill text-xs no-underline">Golden Retriever</a>
          <a href="/german-shepherd-age-calculator" class="tag-pill text-xs no-underline">German Shepherd</a>
          <a href="/french-bulldog-age-calculator" class="tag-pill text-xs no-underline">French Bulldog</a>
          <a href="/dachshund-age-calculator" class="tag-pill text-xs no-underline">Dachshund</a>
          <a href="/chihuahua-age-calculator" class="tag-pill text-xs no-underline">Chihuahua</a>
          <a href="/pomeranian-age-calculator" class="tag-pill text-xs no-underline">Pomeranian</a>
          <a href="/yorkshire-terrier-age-calculator" class="tag-pill text-xs no-underline">Yorkshire Terrier</a>
          <a href="/pug-age-calculator" class="tag-pill text-xs no-underline">Pug</a>
          <a href="/rottweiler-age-calculator" class="tag-pill text-xs no-underline">Rottweiler</a>
          <a href="/great-dane-age-calculator" class="tag-pill text-xs no-underline">Great Dane</a>
          <a href="/husky-age-calculator" class="tag-pill text-xs no-underline">Husky</a>
          <a href="/shih-tzu-age-calculator" class="tag-pill text-xs no-underline">Shih Tzu</a>
          <a href="/border-collie-age-calculator" class="tag-pill text-xs no-underline">Border Collie</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
  "itemListElement": [
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://dogbreedage.com" },
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Corgi Age Calculator", "item": "https://dogbreedage.com/corgi-age-calculator" }
  ]
})} />

<script>
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
  const form = document.getElementById('breed-calc-form');
  const result = document.getElementById('breed-result');
  const haEl = document.getElementById('breed-human-age');
  const stageEl = document.getElementById('breed-stage');
  const expEl = document.getElementById('breed-expectancy');
  const multiplier = 0.92;
  const lifespan = [12, 15];
  const sizeLabel = 'medium';
  const thresholds = [0.5,2,4,7,11,99];
  const stages = ['Puppy','Teenager','Young Adult','Adult','Senior','Elder'];

  form.addEventListener('submit', (e) => {
    e.preventDefault();
    const years = parseInt(document.getElementById('breed-years').value);
    const months = parseInt(document.getElementById('breed-months').value);
    const name = document.getElementById('breed-name').value.trim() || 'Your Corgi';
    if (isNaN(years) || years < 0) { alert('Please enter a valid age'); return; }
    if (years === 0 && months === 0) { alert('Age must be greater than 0'); return; }
    const total = years + months / 12;
    const ha = Math.round((16 * Math.log(Math.max(total, 0.083)) + 31) * multiplier * 10) / 10;
    let stage = 'Elder';
    for (let i = 0; i < thresholds.length; i++) { if (total <= thresholds[i]) { stage = stages[i]; break; } }
    document.querySelector('#breed-result p:first-child').textContent = `${name} is equivalent to`;
    haEl.textContent = ha;
    stageEl.textContent = `Life Stage: ${stage}`;
    expEl.textContent = `Life expectancy: ${lifespan[0]}-${lifespan[1]} years`;
    result.classList.remove('hidden');
    result.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth' });
  });
});
</script>
